OL,5,Crow
OL,7,FAfter the claims reached the Court of
OL,8,FAppeal, three senior judges ruled that
OL,9,Fthe lenders were liable to repay the
OL,10,Fmotorists the commission, as there was
OL,11,F"no disclosure" of the commission
OL,12,Fpayments in Ms Hopcraft's case, and
OL,13,F"insufficient disclosure" in the case
OL,14,Fof Mr Wrench.
OL,16,FIn Mr Johnson's case, the judges found
OL,17,Fthat he had received "insufficient
OL,18,Fdisclosure" about the commission to
OL,19,Fgive "fully informed consent" to the
OL,20,Fpayment.
